-NO, IT'S MINE.

04:22.436 --> 04:23.219
-NO, IT'S NOT.

04:23.350 --> 04:24.307
-LEAVE IT ALONE.

04:24.438 --> 04:26.178
-HEY, HEY, THIS ISN'T YOURS.

04:26.309 --> 04:28.355
LET'S GO, COME ON.

04:30.357 --> 04:31.706
IT'S NOT A HOTEL, HUH.

04:32.533 --> 04:34.186
LET'S MOVE IT.

04:34.317 --> 04:36.188
WHY DON'T YOU GO DOWN TO
ONE OF THOSE SHELTERS, HUH?

04:39.670 --> 04:40.715
-MINE!

04:40.845 --> 04:42.978
[GASPING]

04:56.296 --> 04:57.079
-SAME TIME TOMORROW.

04:57.209 --> 04:57.993
-YEAH, YOU GOT IT.

04:58.123 --> 05:00.300
WHOA! HEY!

05:00.430 --> 05:02.214
WHERE'S HE OFF TO
IN SUCH A HURRY?

05:02.867 --> 05:05.087
-THE NEW "SURF RIDER"
MAGAZINE JUST HIT THE RACKS.

05:06.088 --> 05:08.220
-I DIDN'T KNOW HOBIE
WAS THAT INTO SURFING.

05:08.351 --> 05:09.961
-IT'S THE SWIMSUIT EDITION.

05:10.092 --> 05:11.789
WEIRD, IT'S LIKE
OVERNIGHT HE'S GONE

05:11.920 --> 05:14.749
FROM LOOKING AT SCAGS
TO CHECKING OUT LEGS.

05:15.402 --> 05:17.752
-WELL, MAYBE I SHOULD
HAVE A TALK WITH HIM.

05:17.882 --> 05:18.840
-ABOUT WHAT?

05:18.970 --> 05:21.146
-YOU KNOW, FACTS OF LIFE.

05:21.277 --> 05:22.626
[LAUGHING]

05:22.757 --> 05:24.585
-THANKS, HARVEY, I
THINK I CAN HANDLE THAT.

05:24.715 --> 05:26.151
-WELL, I WAS JUST OFFERING.

05:26.282 --> 05:28.937
I MEAN SOMETIMES IT'S
EASIER FOR A NON-PARENT

05:29.067 --> 05:32.419
TO CUT THROUGH ALL THE
HEMMING AND HAWING.

05:32.549 --> 05:34.725
-THERE'S NOT GONNA BE
ANY HEMMING OR HAWING.

05:34.856 --> 05:36.771
I'M PERFECTLY COMFORTABLE
TALKING TO MY SON

05:36.901 --> 05:38.773
ABOUT ANYTHING AND
EVERYTHING, THANK YOU.

05:53.788 --> 05:55.398
-MAN: THANKS,
THANKS A LOT, NOW TAKE CARE.

05:56.878 --> 05:58.532
3.50 SIR, PLEASE.

06:00.272 --> 06:02.449
3.75 SIR, HERE YOU GO.

06:02.579 --> 06:03.406
THERE'S YOUR CHANGE.

06:04.973 --> 06:06.757
HERE YOU GO, THANKS A LOT.

06:06.888 --> 06:08.324
BURRITOS UP!

06:08.455 --> 06:12.197
HERE YOU GO, SIR.
THANK YOU VERY MUCH, 35.

06:12.328 --> 06:13.851
THANK YOU, THANK YOU VERY MUCH.

06:13.982 --> 06:16.201
HAVE A GOOD DAY, MA'AM.
GET 'EM WHILE THEY'RE HOT!

06:20.684 --> 06:21.816
3.50, SIR.

06:22.686 --> 06:25.820
THANK YOU VERY MUCH.
-THANKS.

06:28.649 --> 06:30.390
-HEY YOU! HOLD IT,
WHAT'D YOU PUT IN HERE, HUH?

06:30.520 --> 06:31.652
-NOTHING! LET GO OF ME!

06:31.782 --> 06:32.740
-WHAT ELSE DID YOU STEAL, HUH?

06:32.870 --> 06:34.002
WHAT ELSE IS THERE?

06:34.132 --> 06:34.959
-IT'S MINE!

06:35.090 --> 06:36.178
[GRUNTING]
-OW!

06:36.308 --> 06:37.614
I CATCH YOU AROUND HERE AGAIN

06:37.745 --> 06:39.311
I'LL HAVE YOU ARRESTED,
YOU LITTLE THIEF!

06:42.924 --> 06:43.881
NEXT.

06:53.282 --> 06:54.457
-LIFEGUARD: THAT OUGHTA DO IT,

06:54.588 --> 06:55.545
JUST CHANGE THE
BANDAGE TWICE A DAY.

06:57.112 --> 06:58.069
-PATIENT: THANKS.

06:59.941 --> 07:01.333
-JUST BECAUSE SOME HOMELESS GUY

07:01.464 --> 07:02.465
TOOK MY PICTURE DOESN'T
MAKE HIM DANGEROUS.

07:02.596 --> 07:04.772
-OH! HOMELESS, YOU KNOW WHAT?

07:04.902 --> 07:07.035
I AM REALLY SICK AND TIRED
OF EVERY VAGRANT AND CRIMINAL

07:07.165 --> 07:09.298
ON THE STREET BEING
CALLED THE HOMELESS.

07:10.517 --> 07:12.344
THIS GUY DOESN'T
BELONG IN A SHELTER,

07:12.475 --> 07:14.303
HE BELONGS IN AN ASYLUM. OW!

07:14.434 --> 07:16.218
-EDDIE, THIS IS GONNA
NEED STITCHES, IT'S DEEP.

07:17.175 --> 07:18.655
-YOU'RE RIGHT.

07:19.917 --> 07:21.832
BUT YOU DIDN'T SEE
THIS GUY, HE WAS CRAZY.

07:22.746 --> 07:24.008
HE ACTED LIKE YOUR
PICTURE WAS HIS

07:24.139 --> 07:25.706
AND I WAS TAKING
IT AWAY FROM HIM.

07:25.836 --> 07:27.185
-THE ONLY THING THAT
MATTERS IS THAT YOU'RE OKAY.

07:27.316 --> 07:28.317
-WRONG, THE ONLY
THING THAT MATTERS

07:28.448 --> 07:31.755
IS ME CATCHING THIS GUY. OW!

07:32.626 --> 07:34.584
-WELL I DON'T KNOW, WHAT
CAN I TELL YOU, MITCH?

07:34.715 --> 07:36.891
HOW'S THE CITY SUPPOSED
TO HANDLE OVER 3,000

07:37.021 --> 07:39.850
WHEN WE ONLY HAVE
558 SHELTER BEDS?

07:39.981 --> 07:41.722
-I DON'T KNOW, GARNER, BUT
SOMETHING'S GOTTA BE DONE,

07:41.852 --> 07:43.332
AND SOMETHING'S
GOTTA BE DONE SOON.

07:43.463 --> 07:44.420
-MITCH, YOU KNOW
AS WELL AS I DO

07:44.551 --> 07:46.204
THERE ARE NO EASY ANSWERS HERE.

07:46.335 --> 07:48.511
-MY GUARDS HAVE PULLED OUT
OVER TWO DOZEN TRANSIENTS

07:48.642 --> 07:50.687
FROM THE WATER IN
THE LAST TWO MONTHS.

07:50.818 --> 07:52.384
NOW WE GOT A STABBING.

07:52.515 --> 07:55.736
I'M TELLING YA, IT'S
GETTING DANGEROUS OUT HERE.

08:02.612 --> 08:05.093
-AL! AL BRING YOUR
PRINT KIT DOWN HERE.

08:05.223 --> 08:06.747
-I'LL BE RIGHT DOWN.

08:12.100 --> 08:13.884
-HEY, LEAH!

08:14.015 --> 08:15.799
WHERE'D YOU GO THIS MORNING,
YOU WERE GONE WHEN I GOT UP.

08:18.019 --> 08:19.803
WHAT'S THIS?

08:19.934 --> 08:21.544
-I BROUGHT YOUR CLOTHES, YOUR
STEREO AND YOUR TOOTHBRUSH.

08:21.675 --> 08:23.067
I CHANGED THE LOCKS
ON THE DOOR,

08:23.198 --> 08:24.547
SO DON'T EVEN BOTHER
TRYING TO USE YOUR KEY.

08:24.678 --> 08:26.462
GOODBYE, HARVEY.

08:27.245 --> 08:30.248
-HEY, MUSCLES, DON'T PUT
THE STEREO IN THE SAND!

08:31.511 --> 08:33.904
LEAH, COME ON, WHY
ARE YOU DOING THIS?

08:34.034 --> 08:35.950
-WHEN YOU MOVED IN WE WERE
SUPPOSED TO SHARE EXPENSES,

08:36.080 --> 08:38.648
SHARE A LIFE TOGETHER,
SHARE EVERYTHING,

08:38.779 --> 08:40.258
BUT I GUESS THE THRILL
YOU GET OUT OF GAMBLING

08:40.389 --> 08:41.433
TURNS YOU ON
MORE THAN I DO.

08:41.563 --> 08:43.784
-OH, NOW THAT IS NOT TRUE!

08:43.914 --> 08:45.612
-YOU LOST THE RENT
MONEY AT THE TRACK,

08:45.742 --> 08:48.266
THE GROCERY MONEY AT POKER.
WELL, NOW YOU'VE LOST ME.

08:48.397 --> 08:51.748
GOODBYE, I HOPE THE
THRILL WAS WORTH IT.

08:51.879 --> 08:54.795
-I'M JUST ON A COLD
STREAK, IT'LL TURN AROUND.

08:54.925 --> 08:56.927
LEAH, COME ON, WHERE
AM I GONNA LIVE?

09:05.327 --> 09:10.637
